         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot Garden ¶ 18/2/73. ¶  ¶ You have agreably surprised me, dear Mr Guilfoyle, by sending me the fruit of Amorphospermum antilogum, ¶  a new genus of Sapoteae, established by me in 1870, as n...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">73.02.18</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Guilfoyle</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS 439c, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">18/2/73.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You have agreably surprised me, dear Mr Guilfoyle, by sending me the fruit of <name key="Amorphospermum%20antilogum">Amorphospermum antilogum</name>,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M erected the genus in B70.12.03, p. 113.</p>
               </note> a new genus of <name key="Sapoteae">Sapoteae</name>, established by me in 1870, as now a surmise, that the genus (with its only known species) might extend to N. S. Wales has been verified.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Bentham in the 4th volume of our work<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham (1863-78), vol. 4, p. 279.</p>
               </note> united this plant with <name key="Sersalisia%20serecea">Sersalisia serecea</name> RBr, with which it has much resemblance in flower and leaves, but not in fruit. The latter is so remarkable in its interior structure and its germination is so peculiar, that I gave for these reasons the generic and specific names. A good supply of the seeds would be of value for botanic gardens in Europe, as the germination (quite exceptional in <name key="Sapoteae">Sapoteae</name>) can then there be watched</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall be glad to see your new Orchid and any other rarities, which your experienced eyes may descry.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Amorphospermum%20antilogum">Amorphospermum antilogum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Sapoteae">Sapoteae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Sersalisia%20serecea">Sersalisia serecea</name>
            </p>
         </div>
